# Yamaha PSR-F51 Reverse Engineering

## Day 1

### Initial condition

The keyboard had a progressive failure. Approximately 10–11 keys were still working while the majority produced no sound.

---

### Disassembly

- Removed the bottom cover.
- Removed the internal key modules.
- Located the main PCB.
- Identified the flat cables.
- Identified the speakers.
- Removed and inspected the rubber contact strips.

---

### Inspection

- Visual inspection of the PCB.
- Visual inspection of the key matrix.
- Looked for damaged components.
- Looked for oxidation.
- Light cleaning of accessible parts.

---

### Testing

Performed a manual test by pressing each rubber contact.

61 contacts tested.

Working contacts:

2, 6, 13, 14, 15, 19, 28, 29, 30, 32 and 34.

---

### Reassembly

The keyboard was completely reassembled after inspection.

Further electrical testing will be performed later.